EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign A.10427A/S.8503A, to change the admissions criteria for New York City’s Specialized High Schools.
EventItemMatterName: Change the admissions criteria for NYC’s Specialized High Schools. (A.10427A/S.8503A)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Disabilities and Addiction
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to include drug awareness education concerning opioids in the school curriculum.
EventItemMatterName: DOE to include drug awareness education concerning opioids in the school curriculum.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Metropolitan Transportation Authority (MTA) to add an additional member to the New York City Transit’s Paratransit Advisory Committee (PAC) who would represent pregnant women and families.
EventItemMatterName: MTA to add an additional member to the NYC Transit’s Paratransit Advisory Committee (PAC) who would represent pregnant women and families.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the United States Department of Homeland Security to investigate abuse allegations and take action to ensure the safety of lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender immigrants in the custody of the United States Department of Homeland Security.
EventItemMatterName: Urging the US Dept of Homeland Security to investigate abuse allegations and take action to ensure the safety of lesbian, gay, bisexual, and transgender immigrants in the custody of the US Dept of Homeland Security.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the State Legislature to enact, and for the Governor to sign, legislation to establish an Electric School Bus Worker Cooperative program.
EventItemMatterName: Establish an Electric School Bus Worker Cooperative program.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to create a pilot program for a worker- and parent-controlled electric school bus company to provide services to New York City school children beginning in September 2018.
EventItemMatterName: DOE to create a pilot program for a worker- and parent-controlled electric school bus company to provide services to NYC school children beginning in September 2018.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign, legislation to amend the Domestic Relations Law and the Family Court Act to prevent the Division of Child Support Enforcement from suspending driving privileges for individuals who need a functioning New York State driver’s license in order to earn a living.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the Domestic Relations Law and the Family Court Act to prevent the Division of Child Support Enforcement from suspending driving privileges for individuals who need a functioning NYS driver’s license in order to earn a living.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution declaring the last day in February as Rare Disease Day in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Declaring the last day in February as Rare Disease Day in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation to amend the Education Law to require more than one school staff person to be trained to administer CPR at all schools during regular school hours.
EventItemMatterName: Require more than one school staff person to be trained to administer CPR at all schools during regular school hours.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Metropolitan Transportation Authority to study and expand the designation of entry-only and exit-only turnstiles at busy subway stations during peak times.
EventItemMatterName: MTA to study and expand the designation of entry-only and exit-only turnstiles at busy subway stations during peak times.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon New York City to allow city employees without children to take one-time paid six-week leave similar to Paid Parental Leave
EventItemMatterName: NYC to allow city employees without children to take one-time paid six-week leave similar to Paid Parental Leave.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution declaring the fourth week in May as Stroke Awareness Week in the City of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Declaring the fourth week in May as Stroke Awareness Week in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution declaring the first Tuesday in May as World Asthma Day in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Declaring the first Tuesday in May as World Asthma Day in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Emergency Management
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the City of New York to commemorate July 31st as New York City Firefighters Recognition Day.
EventItemMatterName: NYC to commemorate July 31st as NYC Firefighters Recognition Day.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the state of New York to provide blood pressure machines in public places throughout the state.
EventItemMatterName: NYS to provide blood pressure machines in public places throughout the state.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution declaring May 4th New York City Teachers, Educational Administrators and Education Support Staff Recognition Day in order to recognize and highlight the important work they do to keep our city’s schools running and to educate our children and provide a suitable environment for learning.
EventItemMatterName: Declaring May 4th NYC Teachers, Educational Administrators and Education Support Staff Recognition Day

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education, as well as the New York State and federal governments, to include instruction in peaceful conflict resolution as part of the required curriculum in all schools.
EventItemMatterName: Include instruction in peaceful conflict resolution as part of the required curriculum in all schools.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State of New York to include in its curriculum requirements, swimming lessons and water safety education to all students in public schools from kindergarten through 12th grade where appropriate and swimming-related instruction, such as water safety and dry land strokes to all students in public schools from kindergarten through 12th grade when their school does not have a pool in the building or is not within 10 miles of a pool where appropriate.
EventItemMatterName: Include in its curriculum requirements, swimming lessons and water safety education to all students in public schools from kindergarten through 12th grade.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to add the history of Haiti, including the Haitian Revolution and the abolition of slavery, to the public schools’ Black History Month curriculum.
EventItemMatterName: DOE to add the history of Haiti, including the Haitian Revolution and the abolition of slavery, to the public schools’ Black History Month curriculum.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York City Department of Education to acknowledge the participation of Haitian soldiers in the Siege of Savannah and the impact of the Haitian Revolution on the Louisiana Purchase, by adding these events to the public schools’ social studies curriculum.
EventItemMatterName: DOE to acknowledge the participation of Haitian soldiers in the Siege of Savannah and the impact of the Haitian Revolution on the Louisiana Purchase, by adding these events to the public schools’ social studies curriculum.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Youth Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution declaring Youth Day in New York City, to be held annually each year on August 12th, coinciding with International Youth Day.
EventItemMatterName: Declaring Youth Day in NYC, to be held annually each year on August 12th, coinciding with International Youth Day.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution recognizing the first week of this and every February as Heart Disease Awareness Week in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Recognizing the first week of this and every February as Heart Disease Awareness Week in NYC.

EventItemMatterName: Establishing a Rosa Parks Day to commemorate the Civil Rights leader.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature and the Governor to expand the Compassionate Care Act, which legalized the medicinal use of marijuana.
EventItemMatterName: Expand the Compassionate Care Act.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to provide school principals with the discretion to declare primary days as staff development days, specifically if they believe election operations will significantly disrupt a regular school day.
EventItemMatterName: DOE to provide school principals with the discretion to declare primary days as staff development days.

EventItemMatterName: Stop Sexual Harassment in NYC Act - Ending Forced Arbitration of Sexual Harassment Act of 2017 (S.2203/H.R.4734)

EventItemMatterName: MTA to undertake a comprehensive lead abatement program throughout the subway system.

EventItemMatterName: MTA to establish a Metrocard discount fare program through which eligible non-profit organizations can receive and distribute discounted Metrocards to their clients.
